CMC Holdings of Kenya Names Mary Ngige as Acting Chief Executive Officer

-- B y   E r i c   O m b o k
-- 
2011-03-15T06:39:43Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-15/cmc-holdings-of-kenya-names-mary-ngige-as-acting-chief-executive-officer.html
  CMC Holdings Ltd. (CMCH) ,  Kenya ’s second-
biggest car dealership by sales, appointed Mary Ngige as acting
chief executive officer after Martin Forster left the company as
part of a “normal restructuring” exercise, she said.  “The aim of the board is to improve the performance of the
company and to grow it,” Ngige, currently group finance manager
at CMC, said in a phone interview today from Nairobi, the
capital.  Ngige said she will report to a two-member caretaker
committee comprised of Peter Muthoka and Paul Ndung’u, who are
both directors of the company. Muthoka is also chairman of  Kenya
Commercial Bank Ltd. (KNCB)   CMC in January reported full-year profit fell 25 percent to
406.7 million shillings ($4.72 million) as the cost of sales
increased by 9.7 percent. Shares in the company declined 40
cents, or 4 percent, to 9.6 shillings at 9:37 a.m. on the  Nairobi Stock Exchange . The stock has slumped 22 percent so far
this year, underperforming the benchmark NSE 20 index, which has
dropped 10 percent over the same period.  Sales of motor vehicles in Kenya, East Africa’s biggest
economy, increased to 11,050 units in the 12 months through
December from 10,264 a year earlier, according to the Kenya
Motor Industry Association’s  website .  To contact the reporter on this story:
Eric Ombok in Nairobi at 
 eombok@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Paul Richardson at 
 pmrichardson@bloomberg.net . 